            <sentence>
                <offset>0</offset>
                <text>Patient S, a 7 -month-old male infant, was referred for evaluation of excessive crying and bilateral painful, non-progressive shin swellings noted since the 3rd month of life.</text>
                <annotation id="1">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="7" offset="101"/>
                    <text>painful</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="4">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="Comment">! Add term requested</infon>
                    <location length="14" offset="126"/>
                    <text>shin swellings</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="3">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="4" offset="126"/>
                    <text>shin</text>
                </annotation>
                <relation id="2">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.PhenotypeRelations</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0002653</infon>
                    <node refid="3" role="source"/>
                    <node refid="1" role="target"/>
                </relation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>176</offset>
                <text>There was no history of associated fever or rashes, swollen joints or swellings elsewhere in the body.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>279</offset>
                <text>No cardiovascular, respiratory or gastrointestinal symptoms were present.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>353</offset>
                <text>The antenatal, perinatal and neonatal periods had been uneventful and all developmental milestones had been attained normally.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>480</offset>
                <text>There was no history suggestive of preceding trauma, drug intake or physical abuse.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>564</offset>
                <text>This child was the first offspring of non-consanguineous parents.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>630</offset>
                <text>There was no history of either parent or any other family member having had similar problems during his/her childhood.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>752</offset>
                <text>The growth parameters were appropriate for age, with the anthropometric measurements corresponding to 25th–50th centile values for 7 months and the nutritional status was good.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>929</offset>
                <text>Examination revealed tender, diffuse, immobile swellings over the anterior aspect of both the legs, which were hard in consistency (Fig. 1).</text>
                <annotation id="5">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="Comment">! Add term requested</infon>
                    <location length="9" offset="47"/>
                    <text>swellings</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="7">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="4" offset="94"/>
                    <text>legs</text>
                </annotation>
                <relation id="6">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.PhenotypeRelations</infon>
                    <node refid="7" role="source"/>
                    <node refid="5" role="target"/>
                </relation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1070</offset>
                <text>The neighboring knee and ankle joints appeared to be normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1131</offset>
                <text>There were no swellings over the jaw, clavicles or ribs or elsewhere on the body.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1213</offset>
                <text>There was no evidence of joint laxity or skin hyper extensibility.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1280</offset>
                <text>The rest of the general and systemic examination findings were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1351</offset>
                <text>There were no clinical signs suggestive of physical abuse.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1410</offset>
                <text>On developmental assessment, the psychomotor development was found to be appropriate for age.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1508</offset>
                <text>Skeletal survey radiographs showed evidence of significant periosteal elevation, new bone formation and cortical thickening involving the diaphyses of the tibial bones bilaterally, along with a milder degree of cortical hyperostosis involving both the femoral bones (Fig. 1).</text>
                <annotation id="8">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="20" offset="59"/>
                    <text>periosteal elevation</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="11">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0031485</infon>
                    <location length="18" offset="81"/>
                    <text>new bone formation</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="12">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="Comment">! Add term requested</infon>
                    <location length="19" offset="104"/>
                    <text>cortical thickening</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="14">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="29" offset="138"/>
                    <text>diaphyses of the tibial bones</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="10">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="29" offset="138"/>
                    <text>diaphyses of the tibial bones</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="15">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="21" offset="211"/>
                    <text>cortical hyperostosis</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="17">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="252"/>
                    <text>femoral bones</text>
                </annotation>
