                    <node refid="17" role="source"/>
                    <node refid="15" role="target"/>
                </relation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1784</offset>
                <text>The knee and ankle joints were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1823</offset>
                <text>The other long bones of the limbs, the ribs and the mandible did not show any significant periosteal changes.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1933</offset>
                <text>The serum alkaline phosphatase level was elevated (630 U/L; normal range 145–420 U/L); but the serum calcium (9.5 mg/dL) and phosphorus (5.5 mg/dL) levels were within the normal range.</text>
                <annotation id="18">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="32" offset="4"/>
                    <text>serum alkaline phosphatase level</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="19">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="8" offset="41"/>
                    <text>elevated</text>
                </annotation>
                <relation id="20">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.PhenotypeRelations</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0003155</infon>
                    <node refid="18" role="source"/>
                    <node refid="19" role="target"/>
                </relation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>2118</offset>
                <text>VDRL serology was negative.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>2146</offset>
                <text>The hemogram, erythrocyte sedimentation rate, random blood sugar, serum creatinine, liver function tests and urine examination findings were all within the normal reference range.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>2329</offset>
                <text>As the clinical and radiological findings suggested the diagnosis of infantile cortical hyperostosis, genetic screening of COL1A1 was performed.</text>
                <annotation id="21">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0100774</infon>
                    <location length="21" offset="79"/>
                    <text>cortical hyperostosis</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>2474</offset>
                <text>The sequencing of exon 41 of COL1A1, as described by Gensure et al., confirmed the heterozygous mutation c.3040 C&gt;T (p.R1014C) in the proband</text>
            </sentence>
